                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3kk9545t/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>To the <addressee>Revd Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Esteemed Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Accept my<lb/> thanks for the use of your “Reason &amp; <lb/> Faith”\n                &amp; let the assurance that they<lb/> have illumined the benighted path<lb/> of a\n                care worn <sic>traveller</sic> console you<lb/> for the loss of their use, for\n                the<lb/> last 2 months, I hope I have<lb/> benefited by the close perusal of<lb/>\n                this little work, as well as the<lb/> many others you were so kind as<lb/> to loan\n                me. I trust you have<lb/> not suffered your pen to lie dormant<lb/> since I left But\n                are providing a<lb/> rich repast for those who like my-<lb/>self hail each effort of\n                your mind,<lb/> as a new light which will guide<lb/> them on their path to\n                Celestial<lb/> Glory. I hope your health has im-<lb/>proved from your late\n                excursion<lb/> My parents sisters &amp; <persName>Sarah Anna</persName> requ<lb/>est\n                to be kindly remembered — I am</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3kk9545t/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
